    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>Oct 2/56</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <sic>
                    <addressee>Revd. Ic Leeser</addressee>
                </sic>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Phila.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your favor of <date>Sept 11</date> has<lb/> been duly received,
                according<lb/> to your order I have supplied<lb/> the two gentlemen with prayer<lb/>
                books <persName>Mr Samuels</persName> however ob-<lb/>jected very much to the high
                price<lb/> charged for binding, he took one<lb/> set in morocco plain marbled
                edges<lb/> at $25 but deducted 5 per cent<lb/> for cash which he thinks very<lb/>
                reasonable with the understanding<lb/> however to return it if you object<lb/> to it
                he expects at any rate the<lb/>
                <sic>priviledge</sic> of <sic>exanging</sic> the books<lb/> he now took for a set of
                the<lb/> new edition when published as<lb/> they are likely to have some im</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>provements particularly in re<lb/>gard to the <add>תקע בשופר</add> which has<lb/>
                been <sic>ommitted</sic> he did not wish<lb/> to take a bible as he bought two<lb/>
                from yourself.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have taken one set in morocco<lb/> plain from <persName>Mr
                    Seixas</persName> and two sets<lb/> in sheep and a bible at $10 from<lb/>
                <persName>Mr Isaacs</persName> for which I gave him<lb/> a receipt <persName>Mr
                    Isaacs</persName> has no bibles<lb/> in plain sheep which are in good<lb/> order
                they are all more or less da-<lb/>maged. I have received for one<lb/> set $18 and
                for the other $23.75<lb/> so I have after deducting my com<lb/>mission $35—which I
                shall pay<lb/> out to <persName>Mr Seixas</persName> between now<lb/> and
                    <date>Sunday</date> next unless you wish<lb/> me to remit it to yourself.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have not been able to collect<lb/> more subscribers yet as I
                could<lb/> not spare the time very well to</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>go round, the fact is that I am<lb/> at present depending on my daily<lb/> business
                and every day I miss is an<lb/> actual loss to me, besides it is<lb/> difficult to
                find people who are<lb/> willing and able to lay out 15 or 20<lb/> Doll: at a time
                for <sic>preyer</sic> books<lb/> the rich class are mostly provided<lb/> and others
                can not afford the<lb/>
                <sic>expence</sic> I should think you might<lb/> sell a good many more if you
                would<lb/> make the terms easier so that people<lb/> can pay by weekly or monthly<lb/>
                <sic>instalments</sic>
                <persName>Mr Mulder</persName> in <placeName>Amster<lb/>dam</placeName> sold a great
                many of his books<lb/> in that manner.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">If you will send me a copy of<lb/> your proposed weekly paper I
                will<lb/> endeavour to get subscribers for it<lb/> and propose myself better
                success<lb/> with the same as it is something<lb/> new and more attainable to the
                mid<lb/>dle class</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>No more for the present but<lb/> remain</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">most respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">J M d'Solla</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
